382
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:43,080
Brew liquor.

383
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,700
Brew liquor?

384
00:32:48,660 --> 00:32:55,020
I have no special skills except for brewing liquor, which I learned in childhood.

385
00:32:55,020 --> 00:33:00,200
Since this is Beyond Civil and Military, naturally I have to bring out my best skill.

386
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:03,700
But isn't aged liquor better?

387
00:33:03,700 --> 00:33:06,920
Can you brew good liquor within 12 hours?

388
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,760
That's what you don't know.

389
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:10,640
Aged liquor has its brewing method.

390
00:33:10,640 --> 00:33:15,420
Freshly brewed liquor also has its brewing method.

391
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:18,140
There are thousands of liquors in this world.

392
00:33:18,140 --> 00:33:21,300
Each has its own flavor and it's not necessarily better the more it ages.

393
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:25,860
It's about whether you can drink the one you like.

394
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:30,060
Don't just look at me. The lamb leg you prepared is still on the table.

395
00:33:30,620 --> 00:33:32,220
I'm on it.

396
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,620
This person is good.

397
00:34:08,620 --> 00:34:14,600
This knife skill looks ordinary but the subtleties reveal true mastery.

398
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:17,640
